  {
    "id": "52937",
    "title": "Jerk chicken with rice & peas",
    "category": "Chicken",
    "area": "Jamaican",
    "servings": 4,
    "instructions": [
      "Make the jerk marinade: blend the spring onions, ginger, garlic, onion, red chillies, thyme, lime juice, soy sauce, vegetable oil, brown sugar and allspice with 1 tsp salt to a thick puree. Don't add water — if it won't blend, stop, stir and restart.",
      "Taste and balance: it should be pleasantly salty. Add more chilli for heat, or a little more brown sugar if it's too salty or sour.",
      "Slash the chicken thighs, rub the marinade into every crevice, cover and marinate overnight in the fridge.",
      "Roast the chicken: heat oven to 180C/160C fan/gas 4. Put the thighs in a roasting tin with the lime halves and cook 45 mins until tender and cooked through. (For authentic jerk, barbecue over slow indirect heat with wood chips for about 30 mins instead.)",
      "Meanwhile make the rice & peas: rinse the basmati rice, then tip into a large saucepan with the coconut milk, spring onions, thyme, garlic and allspice — everything except the beans. Season with salt, add 300ml cold water and bring to the boil.",
      "Once boiling, turn down to medium, cover and cook 10 mins.",
      "Stir in the kidney beans, cover, take off the heat and rest 5 mins until the liquid is absorbed.",
      "Squeeze the roasted lime over the chicken and serve with the rice & peas, plus hot sauce if you like it fiery."
    ],
