    "instructions": [
      "Make the flour batter: whisk flour, water and salt until smooth and lump-free. Aim for a thick but still pourable consistency, adding a splash more water if needed. Set aside.",
      "Make the filling batter: whisk the melted butter, oil and your chosen yogurt or cream until smooth and runny, like custard. Rest 10 minutes, then whisk again. Set aside.",
      "Heat the grill to medium. Oil the base of a large deep baking tray. Using a squeeze bottle or ladle, pipe the flour batter in lines to form a star pattern, leaving triangular gaps between the lines. Grill 3-5 minutes until golden.",
